  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7026.57 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 (-3.0B) and max positive gamma at 7050 (+10.8B), dealers are likely buying the dip here as we're above the negative gamma pocket but below the major selling wall. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and will aggressively defend both sides - they'll ramp up buying pressure if we drift toward 7015 and start selling into any push toward the massive 7050 wall (+10.8B). Watch for mean reversion with 7015-7050 as the key range, though a break below 7015 could trigger accelerated selling as dealers flip to short gamma below the 6875 flip strike.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect the market to bounce back toward 7050 but face heavy selling pressure there.",
